🔵 What is KMS in 2 Lines
AWS KMS is a managed service that allows you to create, manage and control encryption keys used to encrypt your data across AWS services.

🔵 What KMS Does

Create encryption keys      ✅
Store keys securely         ✅
Rotate keys automatically   ✅
Control who uses keys       ✅
Audit key usage             ✅
Encrypt / Decrypt data      ✅

🔵 How KMS Works

Your Data
    │
    ▼
KMS encrypts with CMK
(Customer Master Key)
    │
    ▼
Encrypted Data stored
in S3 / EBS / RDS etc
    │
    ▼
Only authorized users
can decrypt using KMS ✅

KMS Key Types

Key Type                      | Who Manages        | Cost
------------------------------------------------------------
AWS Managed Key              | AWS manages        | Free
Customer Managed Key (CMK)   | You manage         | Paid
Custom Key Store             | You + CloudHSM     | Expensive


🔵 KMS with AWS Services

S3          → Encrypt objects using KMS ✅
EBS         → Encrypt volumes using KMS ✅
RDS         → Encrypt database using KMS ✅
Secrets Mgr → Encrypt secrets using KMS ✅
EKS         → Encrypt K8s secrets using KMS ✅
Lambda      → Encrypt env variables using KMS ✅

🔵 KMS in EKS — Very Common Use Case


Kubernetes Secrets
      │
      ▼
Stored in etcd
      │
      ▼
KMS encrypts etcd data ✅
      │
      ▼
Even if etcd is compromised
Data is encrypted ✅


